The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a meeting with the Vice Premier of China and the Vice Minister of Trade of China. The President expressed optimism about the ongoing trade negotiations between the two countries and mentioned that if a deal is reached, it would be the biggest trade deal ever made. He also read a letter from President Xi, in which he expressed his wishes for a successful agreement. The Vice Premier and Ambassador Lighthizer also spoke about the progress made in the negotiations and the importance of enforcement. The President mentioned that the discussions have covered various issues, including intellectual property, technology transfer, agriculture, and services. He also thanked China for its commitment to purchase a large quantity of soybeans from the US. The President stated that a meeting with President Xi is being planned and that the negotiations are moving forward. He also briefly mentioned the possibility of combining his meeting with Chairman Kim of North Korea with his meeting with President Xi.